<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="B" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Basilisk" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Basilisk,</orth> 1) a fabulous serpent, called also <emph>cockatrice</emph> (q. v.) supposed to kill by its look: <cit><quote>make me not sighted like the b.</quote> <bibl n="shak. wt 1.2.388" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. I, 2, 388</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. h5 5.2.17" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 V, 2, 17</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 3.2.52" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B III, 2, 52</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 3.2.52" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B III, 2, 52</bibl> <bibl n="shak. 3h6 3.2.187" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C III, 2, 187</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 1.2.151" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 I, 2, 151</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 2.4.107" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. II, 4, 107</bibl>.<lb />2) a kind of ordnance: <cit><quote>of --s, of cannon, culverin,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h4 2.3.56" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A II, 3, 56</bibl></cit>.*
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>